jQuery plugin that adds HTML5 canvas drawing capability to a webpage.  
Influenced by (http://mrdoob.com/projects/harmony/)

In your HTML HEAD section include jQuery then jsSketchPad.js and any brushes you
want to allow the user to choose from.

Usage (override defaults by specifying options hash):

jQuery("#drawing_container").sketchyPad({
//options
  width:600,
  height:600
});

Or reset plugin options by redefining defaults:

jQuery.fn.sketchyPad.defaults = {
  width: 800,
  height: 400
  /* ... */
}
jQuery('#my_drawing_pad').sketchyPad(); //will use the new defaults


See sample.html for example implementation with color picker bindings.

If you prefer another color picker, simply bind the onChange event to the setColor static function.

jQuery.sketchyPad.setColor(...);

Create custom brushes by adding your own brush file in brushes folder (see brush samples).
  


